claim.claim-text:
1. An imaging display apparatus, comprising:
a display unit for image display configured to be disposed before eyes of a user;
a communication unit that receives a first image from an external apparatus;
a storage unit that stores a second image;
a first image signal generation unit that generates a display image signal based on a captured image signal captured by an imaging section with a field of view direction of the user;
a second image signal generation unit that generates a display image signal of an image different from an image of the display image signal generated by the first image signal generation unit based on the first image received by the communication unit or the second image stored in the storage unit; and
a control unit that allows, simultaneously on the display unit, display of the image of the display image signal generated by the first image signal generation unit and display of the image of the display image signal generated by the second image signal generation unit.

15. An imaging display method, implemented on an imaging display apparatus, comprising:
performing image display by a display unit configured to be disposed before eyes of a user;
receiving, by a communication unit, a first image from an external apparatus;
storing, by a storage unit, a second image;
generating, by a first image signal generation unit, a display image signal based on a captured image signal captured by an imaging section with a field of view direction of the user;
generating, by a second image signal generation unit, a display image signal of an image different from an image of the display image signal generated by the first image signal generation unit based on the first image received by the communication unit or the second image stored in the storage unit; and
displaying simultaneously on the display unit, display of the image of the display image signal generated by the first image signal generation unit and display of the image of the display image signal generated by the second image signal generation unit.

16. A non-transitory computer readable medium, storing a program that when executed by an imaging display apparatus, causes the imaging display apparatus to perform a method comprising:
performing image display by a display unit configured to be disposed before eyes of a user;
receiving, by a communication unit, a first image from an external apparatus;
storing, by a storage unit, a second image;
generating, by a first image signal generation unit, a display image signal based on a captured image signal captured by an imaging section with a field of view direction of the user;
generating, by a second image signal generation unit, a display image signal of an image different from an image of the display image signal generated by the first image signal generation unit based on the first image received by the communication unit or the second image stored in the storage unit; and
displaying simultaneously on the display unit, display of the image of the display image signal generated by the first image signal generation unit and display of the image of the display image signal generated by the second image signal generation unit.
